track_notes: The plateau top of Baugh Fell is large. I chose to operate at 676m ASL on Knoutberry Haw where there is a trig point and walls for shelter. The route is taken from Wainwrights book. Park on the large free car park on Tom Croft Hill (Side of A684). Great views of the Howgills from there. Follow Ringing Keld Gutter uphill in a gradual ascent. With HF kit it took 3 of us 100 minutes in May 2010 to reach the top. We were taking part in the 2010 Wainwright Society Challenge annual fund raising event.

Start SD77649211 from parking place on minor road.
Follow obvious small track west from opposite the parking spot.  It starts off well surfaced... do not be fooled!
After a short climb, the track descends slightly to a small wooden bridge, immediately afterwards turn south. Follow to a five bar gate and then turn west again to cross a small stream and start your journey uphill trying to keep on the quad bike track which is used by the estate to top up the grouse feeders.  The track soon re-joins the broken wall/fence which is followed through one boundary to an obvious corner where you can step over then fence. Now follow the same wall west to the summit, which has no marker.
Most of the route is boggy.
